import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='Body_Mass__g_', by='Species', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of body mass across different species?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Species')
    ax.set_ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend(title='Species', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Beak_Length__mm_'], data['Beak_Depth__mm_'], c=data['Species'].astype('category').cat.codes, cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    ax.set_title('How does beak length vary with beak depth?')
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Species")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    species_mean_flipper_length = data.groupby('Species')['Flipper_Length__mm_'].mean()
    ax = species_mean_flipper_length.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'green', 'red'])
    plt.title('What is the average flipper length for each species?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Species')
    plt.ylabel('Average Flipper Length (mm)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Flipper Length'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    male_data = data[data['Sex'] == 'male']['Beak_Depth__mm_']
    female_data = data[data['Sex'] == 'female']['Beak_Depth__mm_']
    
    plt.hist([male_data, female_data], label=['Male', 'Female'], alpha=0.7, bins=15)
    plt.xlabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of beak depth for male and female penguins?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
